@startuml svc-reservations--put-reservations-reservation_id-status

!include ../theme.puml
skinparam sequence {
    ArrowColor #059669
}

header [[/microservices/svc-reservations/#integration-context ⬆ svc-reservations Integration Context]]

title PUT /reservations/{reservation_id}/status\nUpdate reservation status\n<size:10><color:#7c3aed>ARCHITECT OVERRIDE — enriched with state transition validation and event publishing</color></size>

participant "Client" as Client [[/applications/]]
participant "API Gateway" as GW [[/actors/#api-gateway]] #E0F2FE
participant "svc-reservations" as Svc [[/microservices/svc-reservations/]] #D1FAE5
participant "Kafka" as Kafka [[/architecture/events/]] #F5F3FF
participant "Notifications" as Ntfy [[/microservices/svc-notifications/]] #F1F5F9
database "PostgreSQL" as DB [[/microservices/svc-reservations/#data-store]] #FEF9C3

note over Svc
  [[/services/api/svc-reservations.html View in Swagger UI]]
end note

Client -> GW : PUT /reservations/{reservation_id}/status\n{ new_status }
activate GW #059669
GW -> Svc : route request
activate Svc #059669

Svc -> DB : SELECT * FROM reservations\nWHERE id = reservation_id
activate DB #FEF9C3
DB --> Svc : Reservation record\n(current_status, _rev)
deactivate DB

note right of Svc #FEF3C7 : **State Transition Matrix**\nCONFIRMED → CHECKED_IN ✓\nCONFIRMED → CANCELLED ✓\nPENDING → CONFIRMED ✓\nPENDING → CANCELLED ✓\nCANCELLED → * ✗\nCOMPLETED → * ✗

alt Invalid transition
    Svc --> GW : 409 Conflict\n(invalid_transition,\ncurrent_status, requested_status)
    deactivate Svc
    GW --> Client : 409 Conflict
    deactivate GW
else Valid transition

    Svc -> DB : UPDATE reservations\nSET status = new_status,\nupdated_at = NOW()\nWHERE id = reservation_id\nAND _rev = expected_rev
    activate DB #FEF9C3
    alt Optimistic lock conflict
        DB --> Svc : 0 rows updated
        deactivate DB
        Svc --> GW : 409 Conflict\n(concurrent_modification)
        GW --> Client : 409 Conflict
    else Update successful
        DB --> Svc : 1 row updated
        deactivate DB

        == Event Publishing ==

        Svc ->> Kafka : reservation.status.changed\n(reservation_id, old_status,\nnew_status, guest_id, timestamp)
        note right of Kafka : Consumed by:\nsvc-check-in\nsvc-scheduling-orchestrator\nsvc-analytics

        == Guest Notification ==

        Svc ->> Ntfy : [[/microservices/svc-notifications/#post-notifications-send-a-notification POST /notifications]]\n(guest_id, template =\nreservation_status_update)

        Svc --> GW : 200 OK\n(reservation_id, status,\nupdated_at, _rev)
        deactivate Svc
        GW --> Client : 200 OK
        deactivate GW
    end
end

@enduml
